      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MAGICAL SAIDE (4) turned in a plain performance last time when seventh at Richmond over 520m behind Joanne (30.22) in a NG. Has good box speed and can overcome the tricky draw. Can discover winning form. RAYMAR SHAME (1) showed little early speed at her last couple, the latest finishing sixth (30.02) in a NG at Richmond. Safe beginner who draws ideally on the inside. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. OCCULENT (3) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (29.89) at this track behind Canya Handle It in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Good beginner aided by a nice draw. Can feature again. ZIPPING AUGUSTA (2) hit the frame here last start so don't underestimate.",
